<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="50" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,295,554]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,327,411,437]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[462,710,412,437]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis box="[462,710,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Afrasura amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with four spurs on the hindlegs (two in 
<taxonomicName box="[1241,1375,412,437]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis box="[1241,1375,412,437]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and male forewing underside costal base dark (yellow in 
<taxonomicName box="[771,903,450,475]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis box="[771,903,450,475]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,295,554]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,488,514]" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName box="[463,713,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amaniensis">
<emphasis box="[463,713,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">Afrasura amaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[729,860,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis box="[729,860,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">A. discreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[876,1087,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submarmorata">
<emphasis box="[876,1087,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">A. submarmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1284,489,514]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis box="[1147,1284,489,514]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">A. violacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar in genitalic morphology; the group is East African except for 
<taxonomicName box="[843,936,528,553]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Afrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discreta">
<emphasis box="[843,936,528,553]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="50">discreta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is West African.
</paragraph>
